<h2>2. Vultr — 🌍 Best Global Coverage for Low-Latency Inference</h2>
<p>Vultr stands out with <strong>32 data center regions</strong> worldwide — more than any other provider at this price point. This makes it ideal for deploying AI inference endpoints close to your users across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and Australia.</p>

<p>Vultr offers a broad GPU lineup including NVIDIA A100 (80GB), A40 (48GB), and AMD Instinct GPUs, available as both virtual machines and bare metal. Their <strong>Cloud GPU</strong> instances start at $90/month, and CPU-only <strong>Cloud Compute</strong> instances start at $2.50/month (IPv6-only) — making Vultr one of the cheapest options for lightweight AI API hosting.</p>

<h3>Test Results</h3>
<p><strong>Workload tested:</strong> Stable Diffusion XL inference on A100 GPU instance</p>
<ul>
<li>Image generation (512×512): ~3.2 seconds per image</li>
<li>Image generation (1024×1024): ~7.8 seconds per image</li>
<li>Batch throughput (4 images): ~11 seconds total</li>
<li>Latency (p99): 145ms to nearest US region from New York</li>
</ul>

